From: Nirmoy Das <nirmoy.das@amd.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jan 2020 15:06:04 +0100
Subject: drm/scheduler: improve job distribution with multiple queues
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 56822db194232c089601728d68ed078dccb97f8b
Patch-mainline: v5.6-rc1
References: jsc#SLE-12680, jsc#SLE-12880, jsc#SLE-12882, jsc#SLE-12883, jsc#SLE-13496, jsc#SLE-15322

This patch uses score based logic to select a new rq for better
loadbalance between multiple rq/scheds instead of num_jobs.

Below are test results after running amdgpu_test from mesa drm

Before this patch:

sched_name     num of many times it got scheduled
=========      ==================================
sdma0          314
sdma1          32
comp_1.0.0     56
comp_1.0.1     0
comp_1.1.0     0
comp_1.1.1     0
comp_1.2.0     0
comp_1.2.1     0
comp_1.3.0     0
comp_1.3.1     0
After this patch:

sched_name     num of many times it got scheduled
=========      ==================================
sdma0          216
sdma1          185
comp_1.0.0     39
comp_1.0.1     9
comp_1.1.0     12
comp_1.1.1     0
comp_1.2.0     12
comp_1.2.1     0
comp_1.3.0     12
comp_1.3.1     0

Signed-off-by: Nirmoy Das <nirmoy.das@amd.com>
